The paper discusses the applications of derandomization theory in coding, specifically in the wiretap channel problem, combinatorial group testing problem, error-correcting codes, and explicit construction of codes. These topics are closely related to information theory (cs.IT), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), cryptography (cs.CR), and signal processing (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
